18:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Fellow is best suited for managers, meeting heavy teams, leadership, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Todoist, meanwhile, shines for individuals, freelancers, GTD practitioners, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Fellow describes itself as \"AI meeting management platform for agendas, notes, and action items.\" Todoist, established in 2007, positions itself as \"Simple and powerful task manager with natural language input and smart scheduling.\" With 10 years between them, Todoist brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Fellow offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
19:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Todoist** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Fellow is a poor choice — far from it. Fellow excels in its own right, particularly for managers and meeting heavy teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best natural language task input, go with Todoist. If excellent meeting note templates matters more to you, Fellow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
